<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-761-726  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 761 726.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Journal of Systems Management  July 1990 v41 n7 p18(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Preserving the environment through systems analysis. (ManagementInformation Round Table) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Reitzfeld, Milt.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Information systems professionals can help save the environment byreducing the amount of paper generated in their operations andreevaluating their methods of administering, communicating,controlling, educating, financing, managing, marketing andplanning.andP;  Only about 23 percent of the paper used in the US isrecycled, and much recycled paper remains unused as people choosevirgin material in its stead.andP;  To help reduce paper consumption,use recycled paper in place of virgin material whenever possible,reduce the size of documents and distribute them less widely,develop and publish practice standards to eliminate as manyreports as possible through use of the exception principle, useprinted forms whenever practical, give all documents a disposaldate and keep only a very few documents permanently, do notoverwhelm customers and clients with trivial information,eliminate legal size documents, use postal cards wheneverpossible, use the telephone more in place of letters, replacemultiple systems with a single integrated system, and supportlegislation mandating use of recycled material.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Environmental ProtectionMISPlanningEcologyRecyclingPaper Media.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>